e%20beaches%2C%20pristine%20blue%20skies%2C%20and%20the%20ocean.%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20intent%20was%20to%20get%20Indians%20to%20put%20Lakshadweep%20high%20on%20the%20catalogue%20of%20places%20they%20must%20as%20part%20of%20their%20vacation.%20His%20visit%20and%20subsequent%20call%20was%20as%20political%20as%20it%20was%20touristic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHow%20ready%20is%20Lakshadweep%20for%20mass%20tourism%3F%20Lakshadweep%20can%20only%20be%20reached%20by%20ships%20and%20flights%20operated%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20lone%20gateway%20%E2%80%93%20Kochi.%20Only%20Indian%20airlines%20operate%20flights%20from%20Kochi.%20As%20a%20tropical%20archipelago%20of%2036%20atolls%20and%20coral%20reefs%20in%20the%20Laccadive%20Sea%2C%20those%20who%20travel%20to%20Lakshadweep%20must%20acquire%20permits%20to%20visit%20populated%20ten%20islands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%202021%2C%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fnews-updates%2Fwithdraw-lakshwadeep-regulations-2021-letter-president-of-india-177085%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%2527%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fnews-updates%2Fwithdraw-lakshwadeep-regulations-2021-letter-president-of-india-177085%3Finfinitescroll%253D1'%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705649439552000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0TyjpfoBirVVDRWkypQLqF%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20written%20by%20a%20collective%20of%2058%20lawyers%20and%20researchers%20urged%20the%20President%20of%20India%20to%20ensure%20%E2%80%9CPeace%2C%20Progress%20%26amp%3B%20Good%20Governance%E2%80%9D%3A%20They%20underscored%20that%20the%20island%E2%80%99s%20geography%2C%20ecology%2C%20and%20sociological%20factors%20placed%20likely%20limits%20on%20the%20kinds%20of%20distinctive%20development%20that%20the%20archipelago%20could%20accommodate.%20Meanwhile%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20massively%20indifferent%20response%20to%20the%20Lakshadweep%20Development%20Authority%20Regulation%20(LDAR)%20scheme%20to%20develop%20eco-tourism%20attractions%20such%20as%20water%20villas.%20A%20water%20villa%20offers%20water%20retreats%20of%20all%20the%20comforts%20that%20one%20desires.%20These%20magnificent%20villas%2C%20built%20on%20stilts%2C%20are%20within%20sight%20of%20a%20coral%20reef%20with%20its%20colorful%20marine%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F18140551%2FGC_Gf8pbsAAgJ18.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F18140551%2FGC_Gf8pbsAAgJ18.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F18140551%2FGC_Gf8pbsAAgJ18-300x217.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F18140551%2FGC_Gf8pbsAAgJ18-1024x742.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-693495%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22869%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20Lakshadweep.%20Photo%3A%20X%20(Twitter)%2F%40narendramodi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELarge-scale%20tourism%20and%20its%20impact%20on%20the%20island%E2%80%99s%20ecology%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ETourism%20as%20a%20form%20of%20luxury%20must%20be%20suitably%20moderated%20and%20controlled.%20Jose%20Dominic%20of%20CGH%20Earth%20Group%2C%20whose%20company%20used%20to%20run%20a%20resort%20in%20Lakshadweep%2C%20fervently%20promotes%20nature%20and%20the%20environment%20in%20his%20business%20and%20asserts%20that%20opulence%20must%20never%20override%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20planet%20and%20society.%20Like%20other%20naturalists%20and%20conservationists%2C%20CGH%20works%20on%20core%20values%20including%20respect%20for%20the%20environment%2C%20local%20community%2C%20and%20adoption%20of%20the%20local%20ethos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMainstream%20tourism%20shows%20disregard%20for%20the%20notion%20of%20carrying%20capacity%20and%20holds%20up%20profits%20as%20precedence.%20%E2%80%9CTourism%20Carrying%20Capacity%E2%80%9D%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Tourism%20Organization%2C%20is%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20maximum%20number%20of%20people%20that%20may%20visit%20a%20tourist%20destination%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20without%20causing%20destruction%20of%20the%20physical%2C%20economic%2C%20socio-cultural%20environment%20and%20an%20unacceptable%20decrease%20in%20the%20quality%20of%20visitors%E2%80%99%20satisfaction%E2%80%9D.%20If%20Lakshadweep%20were%20to%20evolve%20into%20a%20space%20for%20large-scale%20tourism%2C%20and%20it%20emerges%20as%20a%20crowded%20space%20with%20all%20its%20appendages%2C%20it%20could%20gravely%20harm%20the%20island%E2%80%99s%20ecology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Flakshadweep-lakshadweep-development-authority-regulation-researcher-ldar%5C%22%3EExperts%20Write%20to%20President%20to%20Withdraw%20%E2%80%98Incautious%E2%80%99%20Draft%20Lakshadweep%20Regulation%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThere%20is%20a%20tendency%20for%20the%20tourism%20industry%20to%20push%20for%20dredging%20of%20the%20sea%20bed%20to%20enable%20the%20arrival%20of%20ships%20and%20cruise%20liners.%20Dredging%20and%20desilting%20can%20have%20serious%20and%20long-lasting%20negative%20impacts%20on%20the%20environment.%20For%20example%2C%20it%20can%20damage%20or%20destroy%20fish%20spawning%20grounds.%20Silt%20can%20become%20suspended%20in%20the%20water%2C%20lowering%20oxygen%20levels%2C%20and%20potentially%20releasing%20harmful%20chemicals%20that%20may%20be%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EScientists%20and%20marine%20biologists%20are%20also%20opposed%20to%20dredging%20because%20coral%20reefs%20provide%20food%20and%20resources%20for%20more%20than%20500%20million%20people%20in%20over%20100%20countries%20and%20territories%20and%20are%20valued%20at%20an%20economic%20value%20of%20%24375%20billion%20a%20year.%20Dredging%20and%20desilting%20also%20have%20serious%20and%20long-lasting%20negatives%20by%20destroying%20fish%20spawning%20grounds%20and%20making%20river%20banks%20unstable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iadc-dredging.com%2F%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.iadc-dredging.com%2F%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705649439552000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1T--YZnRwLaoGarEeNLD-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInternational%20Association%20of%20Dredging%20Companies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CCoral%20reefs%20are%20large%2C%20long-lived%20bio-geological%20structures%20that%20are%20marine%20ridges%20or%20mounds.%20They%20are%20formed%20from%20the%20deposition%20of%20calcium%20carbonate%20by%20living%20organisms%2C%20predominantly%20hard%20corals%2C%20but%20also%20by%20other%20organisms%20such%20as%20coralline%20algae%20and%20shellfish.%E2%80%9D%20Further%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthey%20are%20robust%20and%20have%20often%20withstood%20the%20forces%20of%20storms%2C%20climatic%20change%2C%20sea%20level%20change%20and%20predators%2C%20the%20living%20elements%20%E2%80%93%20coral%2C%20coralline%20algae%20and%20shellfish%20that%20build%20these%20structures%20%E2%80%93%20are%20just%20a%20very%20thin%20veneer%20of%20delicate%20tissue%2C%20highly%20sensitive%20to%20the%20surrounding%20environment.%20The%20destruction%20of%20coral%20reefs%20can%20be%20life-threatening%20to%20nature%2C%20sea%20life%2C%20and%20humans.%20Any%20form%20of%20their%20degradation%20must%20be%20deemed%20as%20%E2%80%98sacrilegious%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20aggressive%20call%20to%20inflate%20tourism%20to%20levels%20which%20exceed%20carrying%20capacity%20levels%20would%20depressingly%20alter%20the%20serenity%20that%20now%20characterises%20the%20islands.%20There%20are%20only%20some%20selected%20locations%20that%20one%20can%20visit%20on%20the%20main%20island%20of%20Lakshadweep%20%E2%80%93%20Kavaratti%20is%20one%20of%20the%20more%20developed%20islands.%20It%20is%20home%20to%20dozens%20of%20mosques%2C%20including%20the%20Kavaratti%20Aquarium%20which%20showcases%20regional%20fish%2C%20shark%20and%20coral%20species.%20However%2C%20mass%20tourists%20crave%20to%20be%20entertained%20in%20a%20myriad%20of%20other%20ways.%20These%20can%20be%20inexpedient%20to%20the%20ecosystem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20tragic%20case%20of%20Goa%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ETake%20the%20example%20of%20Goa.%20When%20tourism%20arrived%20in%20Goa%20in%20the%201960s%2C%20the%20hippies%20attracted%20young%20people%20with%20the%20cultural%20isolation%2C%20beauty%20of%20tropical%20nature%2C%20and%20the%20atmosphere%20of%20spirituality%20reigning%20there.%20People%20here%20are%20different%2C%20parties%20are%20more%20indie%20and%20yoga%20and%20spiritual.%20The%20hippie%20culture%20in%20Anjuna%2C%20Vagator%2C%20and%20Baga%20in%20North%20Goa%2C%20was%20all%20about%20freedom%2C%20spirituality%20and%20creativity.%20The%20town%2C%20notably%20Anjuna%2C%20still%20has%20its%20home-based%20guesthouses%2C%20cafes%2C%20and%20art%20galleries%20that%20are%20perfect%20for%20people%20who%20live%20a%20bohemian%20lifestyle.%20Hippie-styled%20people%20and%20hippies%20themselves%2C%20who%20came%20to%20Goa%20and%20still%20believe%20in%20the%20ideals%20of%20the%20hippie%20culture%2C%20run%20these%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ETragically%2C%20in%20less%20than%20two%20decades%2C%20a%20short%20108%20km%20coastline%20of%20calm%20and%20serenity%20was%20trounced%20by%20crowds%20with%20large%20hotels%20and%20resorts.%20Coastal%20Goa%20is%20dotted%20with%20casinos%2C%20gambling%20parks%2C%20massage%20parlors%2C%20dance%20clubs%2C%20a%20drug%20trade%2C%20and%20an%20offensive%20sex%20industry.%20Today%2C%20a%201.4%20million%20population%20are%20in%20overdrive%20as%20they%20host%20over%207%20million%20tourists!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBack%20to%20Lakshadweep%20%E2%80%93%20PM%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20invitation%20to%20Indians%20to%20throng%20to%20Lakshadweep%20has%20created%20tensions%20with%20Maldives.%20Union%20minister%20Kishan%20Reddy%20declared%20that%20Lakshadweep%20has%20huge%20tourism%20potential%20and%20called%20on%20Indian%20travelers%20to%20explore%20Lakshadweep%20leaving%20aside%20other%20overseas%20destinations%20for%20exciting%20domestic%20holidays.%20This%20call%20raised%20a%20red%20flag%20in%20Maldives.%20It%20was%20perceived%20as%20an%20unannounced%20competition.%20Ostensibly%20Maldives%20perceived%20a%20threat%20to%20their%20tourism%20market%20%E2%80%93%20a%20market%20frequented%20by%20some%2020%2C000%20Indian%20tourists%20annually%20seeking%20tourist%20pleasures%20that%20Maldives%20has%20readied%20and%20made%20operational.%20Social%20media%20heated%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMaldives%20still%20has%20the%20edge%20and%20Lakshadweep%20cannot%20rapidly%20reach%20Maldives%E2%80%99%20levels%20of%20tourist%20influx%20easily.%20Maldives%20has%20close%20to%201%2C200%20islands%20across%2026%20atolls%20spread%20over%209%2C000%20sq%20km.%20Lakshadweep%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20has%20a%20land%20area%20measuring%2032%20sq%20km.%20The%20only%20way%20Lakshadweep%20can%20compete%20with%20Maldives%20is%20by%20total%20destruction%20of%20the%20reefs%20and%20islands%20of%20Lakshadweep%20in%20less%20than%20a%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELessons%20from%20the%20Maldives%20to%20Lakshadweep%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELakshadweep%20ought%20to%20absorb%20lessons%20from%20the%20horrors%20of%20what%20one%20finds%20hidden%20from%20view%20in%20what%20is%20euphemistically%20termed%20%E2%80%98Maldives%20%E2%80%93%20Always%20Natural%E2%80%99.%20Maldives%20conceals%20stench-filled%20smoke%20cascading%20into%20the%20water%2C%20swarms%20of%20flies%2C%20and%20toxic%20smoke%20from%20dumps%20of%20garbage.%20The%20Thilafushi%20Corporation%2C%20a%20body%20that%20works%20on%20the%20island%20and%20estimates%20the%20garbage%20coming%20to%20the%20island%20is%20about%20%E2%80%9C300-400%20tons%20of%20trash%20per%20day%E2%80%9D.%20Rising%20sea%20levels%20endanger%20Thilafushi%20which%20will%20lead%20waste%20from%20the%20landfill%20into%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20when%20they%20overspill%20and%20result%20in%20environmental%20havoc.%20The%20total%20plastic%20footprint%20in%20the%20Maldives%20is%20about%2012%25%20of%20the%20total%20waste%20amounting%20to%20nearly%2043%2C134%20tons%20per%20year%20(%3Ca%3EMaldives%20Ocean%20Plastics%20Alliance%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A02021).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F18140744%2FGC_DVa3a0AAE8IT.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F18140744%2FGC_DVa3a0AAE8IT.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F18140744%2FGC_DVa3a0AAE8IT-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F18140744%2FGC_DVa3a0AAE8IT-1024x684.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-693500%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22801%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAn%20aerial%20view%20of%20beaches%20in%20Lakshadweep.%20Photo%3A%20X%20(Twitter)%2F%40narendramodi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMaldives%20has%20become%20emblematic%20of%20the%20challenges%20that%20sea%20level%20rise%20will%20bring%20to%20many%20countries.%20The%20former%20president%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphys.org%2Fvisualstories%2F2021-10-maldives-threatened-seas-coastal-environmental.amp%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fphys.org%2Fvisualstories%2F2021-10-maldives-threatened-seas-coastal-environmental.amp%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705649439552000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3ISyg6G5-0yGJirghnk44k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMaldives%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Mohamed%20Nasheed%2C%C2%A0a%20champion%20of%20Island%20nations%2C%20speaking%20for%2050%20climate-vulnerable%20countries%20at%20a%20UN%20conference%20averred%20that%20those%20living%20in%20threatened%20coastal%20areas%20and%20islands%20%E2%80%9Care%20paying%20with%20our%20lives%20for%20the%20carbon%20someone%20else%20emitted%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EClimate%20change%20is%20accelerating%20the%20rise%20in%20sea%20levels%20around%20the%20world%2C%20leaving%20some%20of%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20populations%20to%20live%20in%20marginal%20areas%20where%20flooding%20from%20high%20tides%20is%20increasing.%20Higher%20sea%20levels%20coincide%20with%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.nationalgeographic.com%2F2018%2F06%2Fhurricanes-cyclones-move-slower-drop-more-rain-climate-change-science%2F%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fnews.nationalgeographic.com%2F2018%2F06%2Fhurricanes-cyclones-move-slower-drop-more-rain-climate-change-science%2F%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705649439552000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1-RHn_jo8BxpPEk0Mk022A%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0hurricanes%20and%20typhoons%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20result%20in%20more%20rain%2C%20contributing%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fngm.nationalgeographic.com%2F2012%2F09%2Fextreme-weather%2Fmiller-text%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Fngm.nationalgeographic.com%2F2012%2F09%2Fextreme-weather%2Fmiller-text%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705649439552000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2HsXkFLKjGulHezMUoO9dr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estorm%20surges%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20can%20strip%20away%20everything%20in%20their%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20UNDP%2C%20Lakshadweep%2C%20just%201-2%20meters%20above%20sea%20level%20on%20average%20%E2%80%93where%20every%20seventh%20person%20is%20a%20fisherman%20%E2%80%93%20is%20losing%20its%20coral%20reefs%20and%20facing%20varieties%20of%20climate%20change%20at%20multiple%20levels.%20Tourists%2C%20in%20general%2C%20are%20especially%20fascinated%20by%20corals%20and%20the%20colorful%20reefs.%20They%20are%20beautiful%20and%20biologically%20diverse%20habitats%20in%20the%20ocean%2C%20as%20well%20as%20some%20of%20the%20most%20ancient.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ELakshadweep%20used%20to%20be%20the%20perfect%20example%20of%20how%20coral%20islands%20are%20formed%20and%20how%20the%20corals%20nurture%20marine%20life%20and%20also%20the%20people%20who%20depend%20on%20them.%20Corals%2C%20and%20the%20atolls%20and%20lagoons%20they%20form%2C%20are%20now%20in%20grave%20danger%20from%20global%20warming.%20In%20October%2C%20the%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20body%20of%20climate%20scientists%20and%20experts%2C%20dropped%20a%20bombshell%20in%20a%20special%20report%20called%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipcc.ch%2Fsr15%2F%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipcc.ch%2Fsr15%2F%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705649439552000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3RkRWTPC6j-RJP28aAJTBD%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGlobal%20Warming%20of%201.5%C2%BAC%3C%2Fa%3E%20citing%20risks.%20The%20report%20delivered%20at%20the%20United%20Nations%E2%80%99%2048th%20session%20of%20the%20IPCC%20offered%20an%20%E2%80%9Cauthoritative%2C%20scientific%20guide%20for%20governments%E2%80%9D%20to%20deal%20with%C2%A0climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESadly%2C%20Corals%20and%20coral%20reefs%20near%20Kavaretti%20are%20reportedly%20irreversibly%20endangered%20and%20activists%20are%20finding%20them%20hard%20to%20restore.%20Preserving%20delicate%20habitats%20such%20as%20coral%20reefs%20can%20be%20a%20challenging%20task%20for%20scientists.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20challenges%20is%20the%20sheer%20size%20and%20complexity%20of%20coral%20reefs.%20Coral%20reefs%20are%20some%20of%20the%20most%20bio-diverse%20environments%20on%20Earth%2C%20and%20they%20support%20a%20staggering%20array%20of%20plant%20and%20animal%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFor%20mass%20tourism%20in%20Lakshadweep%20to%20take%20off%2C%20an%20airport%20which%20can%20cope%20with%20heavy%20aircraft%20will%20be%20required.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftransportenvironment.org%2Fchallenges%2Fplanes%2Fairplane-pollution%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DEmissions%2520from%2520aviation%2520are%2520a%2Caltitude%2520at%2520which%2520aircraft%2520operate.%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Ftransportenvironment.org%2Fchallenges%2Fplanes%2Fairplane-pollution%2F%2523%3A~%3Atext%253DEmissions%252520from%252520aviation%252520are%252520a%2Caltitude%252520at%252520which%252520aircraft%252520operate.%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705649439552000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2-uoMiXb8nZCn04HD63Tjo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAirplanes%20burn%C2%A0fossil%20fuel%C2%A0which%20not%20only%20releases%20CO2%20emissions%20but%20contributes%20to%20climate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Suggestions%20that%20air%20connectivity%20must%20be%20enhanced%20are%20being%20propagated.%20For%20people%20in%20Lakshadweep%2C%20all%20this%20is%20a%20potential%20nightmare.%20Indian%20corporations%20from%20the%20mainland%20are%20placing%20profits%20over%20people%20and%20the%20ecosystem.%20Fears%20of%20cruise%20lines%20stepping%20in%20will%20mean%20redeveloping%20the%20island%E2%80%99s%20port%20to%20accommodate%20huge%20ships.%20Coral%20dredging%20to%20accommodate%20this%20will%20cause%20irreversible%20damage%20that%20cannot%20be%20altered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAmidst%20the%20disparaging%20remarks%20aimed%20at%20India%20by%20Maldivian%20politicians%20on%20Twitter%2C%20EaseMyTrip%20CEO%20hastily%20terminated%20all%20packages%20to%20the%20Maldives.%20Several%20Indian%20travelers%20canceled%20their%20Maldives%20bookings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Maldives%20social%20media%20users%20reject%20India%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccompete%E2%80%9D%20with%20their%20country%20as%20a%20choice%20for%20tropical%20vacations.%20Zahid%20Rameez%20of%20the%20Progressive%20Party%20of%20Maldives%20(PPM)%2C%20indecorously%20declared%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20move%20is%20great.%20However%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20competing%20with%20us%20is%20delusional.%20How%20can%20they%20provide%20the%20service%20we%20offer%3F%20How%20can%20they%20be%20so%20clean%3F%E2%80%9D%20Rameez%E2%80%99s%20posts%20instigated%20a%20range%20of%20racist%20remarks%20against%20Indians%20and%20Indian%20tourists.%20Indian%20tourists%20have%20remained%20among%20the%20top%20ten%20nationalities%20travelling%20to%20Maldives%20every%20year.%20In%202023%20alone%2C%20Indians%20formed%20the%20largest%20group%20of%20tourists%20with%20over%20200%2C000%20travelers%2C%20followed%20by%20tourists%20from%20Russia%20and%20China.%20The%20Maldives%20is%20profoundly%20dependent%20on%20tourism%20and%20the%20industry%20accounts%20for%20over%2028%20percent%20of%20its%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIndia%20tourism%20planners%20need%20to%20view%20Lakshadweep%20as%20a%20space%20that%20typifies%20the%20most%20ideal%20form%20of%20tourism.%20It%E2%80%99s%20magnificent%3A%20expansive%20sandy%20beaches%2C%20coral%20reefs%20and%20create%20the%20opportunity%20for%20scuba%20diving%2C%20and%20windsurfing%20%E2%80%93%20thrills%20that%20are%20not%20available%20just%20about%20anywhere%20except%20in%20the%20coastal%20areas%20and%20Small%20Islands.%20India%20cannot%20just%20open%20the%20floodgates%20to%20tourism.%20It%20must%20be%20scientifically%20paced.%20There%20is%20an%20obligation%20to%20protect%20the%20Islands%E2%80%99%20fragile%20ecology%20and%20limited%20assets.%20It%E2%80%99s%20no%20shame%20to%20say%20we%20have%20insufficient%20space.%20To%20promote%20%E2%80%98responsible%20Tourism%E2%80%99%20is%20more%20crucial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAny%20plan%20to%20turn%20Lakshadweep%20into%20a%20destination%20that%20rivals%20the%20Maldives%20will%20see%20India%20come%20a%20cropper%3B%20especially%20in%20the%20extent%20of%20environmental%20and%20human%20damage%20it%20will%20cost%20Lakshadweep.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIf%20Indian%20corporations%20eye%20profit%20and%20invest%2C%20they%20could%20end%20up%20indulging%20in%20a%20massive%20overhaul%20of%20the%20infrastructure%20in%20the%20Islands%20which%20is%20currently%20meant%20to%20service%20its%2060%2C000-plus%20local%20residents.%20Indian%20industry%20will%20get%20into%20an%20unequal%20and%20unfair%20competition%20with%20the%20Islanders%20who%20view%20their%20coral%20reefs%20as%20sustenance%20to%20their%20eco-systems%20which%2C%20then%2C%20enable%20them%20to%20harvest%20tuna%2C%20and%20tuna-like%20fishes%20and%20sharks.%20Rather%20than%20being%20able%20to%20boast%20of%20a%20successful%20enterprise%2C%20India%20may%20end%20up%20destroying%20a%20heaven-on-earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ETourism%20which%20is%20not%20structured%20to%20preserve%20the%20ecosystem%2C%20enhance%20local%20communities%2C%20their%20livelihoods%2C%20and%20conserve%20and%20protect%20their%20cultures%2C%20is%20the%20very%20antithesis%20of%20tourism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ERanjan%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0%3Cspan%3ESolomon%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20human%20rights%20activist%2C%20who%20has%20worked%20as%20General%20Secretary%20of%20a%20Global%20Coalition%20on%20Third%20World%20Tourism.%20He%20has%20also%20worked%20pro-bono%20as%20Founder%20and%20Consultant%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Centre%20for%20Responsible%20Tourism%20in%20Goa%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705567423000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F18135318%2FEffect-71.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fany-plans-to-make-lakshadweep-a-tourist-hub-that-rivals-the-maldives-could-prove-costly%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20cannot%20just%20open%20the%20floodgates%20to%20tourism.%20It%20must%20be%20scientifically%20paced.%20There%20is%20an%20obligation%20to%20protect%20the%20Islands'%20fragile%20ecology%20and%20limited%20assets.%20It's%20no%20shame%20to%20say%20we%20have%20insufficient%20space.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fany-plans-to-make-lakshadweep-a-tourist-hub-that-rivals-the-maldives-could-prove-costly%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Arbaaz%20shares%20mushy%20pic%20with%20Sshura%20on%20her%20b'day%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705567388000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106953317%2Cimgsize-45040.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Farbaaz-khan-shares-