Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EAlthough%20wheat%20stocks%20in%20the%20government%20godowns%20have%20been%20over%20and%20above%20the%20minimum%20buffer%20levels%2C%20they%20have%20plunged%20to%20the%20levels%20considered%20the%20lowest%20in%20the%20last%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Food%20Corporation%20of%20India%20(FCI)%20and%20state%20agencies%2C%20the%20godowns%20had%20163.5%20lakh%20tonnes%20(lt)%20of%20the%20cereal%20as%20of%20January%201%2C%20the%20lowest%20for%20this%20date%20since%20the%20137.5%20lt%20of%202017%2C%20the%3Cem%3E%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fwheat-stocks-above-buffer-but-plunge-to-a-7-yr-low-9114706%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20163.5%20lt%2C%20the%20current%20levels%20are%20higher%20than%20the%20minimum%20buffer%20level%20of%20138%20lt%2C%20required%20to%20cover%20three%20months%20of%20operational%20requirement%20of%20108%20lt%20as%20well%20an%20additional%2030%20lt%20required%20in%20case%20of%20any%20procurement%20shortfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20at%20516.5%20lt%2C%20the%20rice%20stocks%20(inclusive%20of%20grain%20derived%20from%20un-milled%20paddy)%20were%20also%20higher%20than%20the%20normative%20minimum%20buffer%20of%2076.1%20lt%20as%20of%20January%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20overall%20stock%20levels%20of%20wheat%20and%20rice%20together%20stood%20at%20680%20lt%2C%20much%20higher%20than%20214.1%20lt%20%E2%80%93%20164.1%20lt%20for%20operational%20requirement%20and%2050%20lt%20strategic%20reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20depletion%20in%20wheat%20stocks%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20retail%20cereal%20prices%20rose%209.93%25%20year-on-year%20in%20December%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20preceded%20by%2015%20consecutive%20months%20of%20double-digit%20inflation%C2%A0from%20September%202022%20to%20November%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20has%20been%20trying%20several%20measures%2C%20including%20banning%20exports%20of%20wheat%20and%20non-basmati%20white%20rice%20to%20stem%20the%20rising%20inflation%20of%20cereals.%20The%20government%20banned%20wholesalers%20and%20big%20chain%20retailers%20from%20holding%20more%20than%201%2C000%20tonnes%20of%20wheat%2C%20and%20also%20selling%20grain%20from%20FCI%E2%80%99s%20stocks%20in%20the%20open%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarket%20experts%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20say%20while%20these%20measures%20may%20bring%20temporary%20relief%20in%20arresting%20food%20inflation%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20it%20depends%20on%20the%20size%20of%20the%20harvest%20of%20the%20wheat%20crop%20at%20March-end%2C%20ahead%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20time%20around%2C%20farmers%20have%20sown%20336.96%20lakh%20hectares%20(lh)%20area%20under%20wheat%2C%20up%20from%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20335.67%20lh%20and%20the%20normal%20five-year%20average%20of%20307.32%20lh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20crop%20that%20was%20sown%20early%20(from%20late%20October%20to%20the%20first%20week%20of%20November)%20is%20coming%20close%20to%20heading%20(i.e.%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98baali%E2%80%99%2C%20or%20earheads%20bearing%20the%20flowers%20and%20eventually%20grain%2C%20to%20fully%20emerge%20from%20the%20wheat%20tillers).%20We%20were%20initially%20worried%20about%20the%20winter%20not%20setting%20in%20and%20temperatures%20ruling%20above%20normal%20till%20about%20mid-December.%20But%20now%2C%20both%20the%20weather%20and%20the%20crop%20(sown%20early%20as%20well%20as%20late%20after%20mid-November)%20look%20very%20good%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rajbir%20Yadav%2C%20principal%20scientist%20at%20the%20New%20Delhi-based%20Indian%20Agricultural%20Research%20Institute%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705563310000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F19161235%2F31764443254_73b92a3ef0_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.i