%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Modi%20Tried%20to%20Surreptitiously%20Cut%20States'%20Share%20of%20Central%20Taxes%20in%202014%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F18121214%2FGDpRC6VakAAZMy8.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3ESoon%20after%20he%20came%20to%20power%20in%202014%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20tried%20to%20significantly%20cut%20states%E2%80%99%20access%20to%20funds%20using%20backdoor%20negotiations%20with%20the%20Finance%20Commission%20of%20India%2C%20a%20new%20expos%C3%A9%20from%20The%20Reporters%E2%80%99%20Collective%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Feconomy%2F2024%2F1%2F18%2Fas-pm-indias-modi-secretly-tried-to-massively-cut-state-funds%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAl%20Jazeera%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20found.%20However%2C%20Modi%20had%20to%20back%20off%20because%20the%20then%20head%20of%20the%20commission%2C%20Y.V.%20Reddy%2C%20resisted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Finance%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20firm%20stance%20forced%20the%20Modi%20government%20to%20hastily%20redo%20its%20maiden%20full%20budget%20in%2048%20hours%20and%20slash%20funding%20across%20welfare%20programmes%20since%20its%20assumption%20of%20retaining%20a%20greater%20portion%20of%20the%20central%20taxes%20did%20not%20pan%20out%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EAl%20Jazeera%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20report%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EB.V.R.%20Subrahmanyam%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20Modi%20government-created%20government%20think-tank%20NITI%20Aayog%2C%20revealed%20this%20back-and-forth%20at%20a%20talk%20organised%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Social%20and%20Economic%20Progress%20last%20year.%20He%20said%20in%20that%20talk%20that%20Union%20government%20budgets%20are%20%E2%80%9Ccovered%20in%20layers%20and%20layers%20of%20attempt%20to%20cover%20the%20truth%E2%80%9D.%20He%20added%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Csure%20you%20will%20have%20a%20Hindenburg%20who%20will%20open%20up%20the%20%5BIndian%20government%E2%80%99s%5D%20accounts%20if%20they%20are%20transparent%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20video%20of%20this%20talk%20was%20available%20on%20YouTube%2C%20but%20was%20pulled%20down%20soon%20after%20The%20Reporters%E2%80%99%20Collective%20sent%20a%20questionnaire%20on%20the%20subject%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office.%20The%20journalists%20independently%20verified%20these%20claims%20using%20documents%20and%20the%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAl%20Jazeera%20reports%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20its%20report%20that%20it%20submitted%20in%20December%202014%2C%20the%20commission%20recommended%20that%20states%20should%20get%2042%20percent%20of%20the%20share%20of%20central%20taxes%2C%20up%20from%20the%2032%20percent%20they%20had%20been%20receiving%20until%20then.%20But%20Modi%2C%20now%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20and%20his%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%2C%20wanted%20to%20keep%20the%20states%E2%80%99%20share%20of%20taxes%20down%20at%2033%20percent%20and%20a%20larger%20portion%20for%20the%20federal%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20constitutional%20provisions%2C%20the%20government%20has%20only%20two%20options%3A%20accept%20the%20Finance%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20or%20reject%20them%20and%20establish%20a%20new%20commission.%20It%20cannot%20argue%2C%20debate%20or%20negotiate%20with%20it%20formally%20or%20informally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20prime%20minister%20tried%20off-record%20parleys%20to%20get%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20Finance%20Commission%2C%20YV%20Reddy%2C%20who%20was%20earlier%20the%20governor%20of%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20to%20pare%20down%20his%20recommendations%20on%20the%20revenue%20share.%20In%20his%20comments%20on%20the%20panel%2C%20Subrahmanyam%20said%20he%20was%20the%20only%20other%20person%20in%20that%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20in%20breach%20of%20constitutional%20propriety.%20If%20the%20government%20had%20succeeded%2C%20it%20would%20be%20able%20to%20reduce%20the%20states%E2%80%99%20income%20while%20passing%20the%20blame%20onto%20the%20constitutional%20body%2C%20the%20commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubrahmanyam%20said%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctripartite%20discussion%20between%20Dr%20Reddy%2C%20me%20and%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%9D%20about%20the%20figure%20took%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNo%20Finance%20Ministry%20%5Bofficial%20or%20minister%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20stressed%2C%20was%20involved.%20%E2%80%9CShould%20it%20be%2042%20%5Bpercent%5D%20or%2032%20%5Bpercent%5D%20or%20some%20number%20in%20between%3F%20The%20previous%20number%20was%2032%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20percentage%20share%20of%20taxes%20recommended%20by%20the%2013th%20Finance%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conversation%20lasted%20two%20hours%2C%20Sabrahmanyam%20said%2C%20but%20Reddy%20was%20unyielding.%20Subrahmanyam%20recalled%20Reddy%2C%20telling%20him%20in%20%E2%80%9Cgood%20south%20Indian%20English%3A%20%E2%80%98Appa%20%5BBrother%5D%2C%20go%20and%20tell%20your%20boss%20%5Bthe%20prime%20minister%5D%20that%20he%20has%20no%20choice%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20had%20to%20accept%20the%20Finance%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20of%2042%20percent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20failed%20backdoor%20negotiations%2C%20Modi%20hid%20from%20parliament%20that%20he%20had%20tried%20to%20reduce%20states%E2%80%99%20share%20of%20taxes.%20He%20said%20in%20parliament%20on%20February%2027%2C%202015%2C%20%E2%80%9CTo%20strengthen%20the%20nation%2C%20we%20have%20to%20strengthen%20the%20states%E2%80%A6%20There%20is%20a%20dispute%20among%20Finance%20Commission%20members.%20We%20could%20have%20taken%20advantage%20of%20that.%20We%20didn%E2%80%99t.%20But%20it%20is%20our%20commitment%20that%20states%20should%20be%20enriched%2C%20should%20be%20strengthened.%20We%20gave%20them%2042%20percent%20devolution.%E2%80%9