elease%20by%20the%20management%20and%20I%20am%20prevented%20from%20speaking%20to%20the%20press%20by%20the%20POSH%20rules%2017(6)%20of%20the%20institute.%20I%20will%20address%20this%20appropriately%20at%20an%20appropriate%20forum%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705553109000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F13132528%2FIIM-Calcutta-Auditorium.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fiim-calcutta-removes-director-sahadeb-sarkar-over-sexual-harassment-complaint%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20next%20senior-most%20faculty%20member%2C%20professor%20Saibal%20Chattopadhyay%2C%20has%20been%20appointed%20as%20director-in-charge.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fiim-calcutta-removes-director-sahadeb-sarkar-over-sexual-harassment-complaint%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20next%20country%20to%20land%20humans%20on%20the%20moon%20in%20the%20next%2010%20years%20'sets%20a%20precedent'%20for%20who%20decides%20the%20rules%20there%3A%20US%20officials%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225691%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22China's%20Chang'e-4%20lunar%20probe%2C%20taken%20by%20the%20Yutu-2%20moon%20rover%2C%20on%20the%20far%20side%20of%20the%20moon.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a8a7886979d737182433ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223179%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChina's%20Chang'e-4%20lunar%20probe%2C%20taken%20by%20the%20Yutu-2%20moon%20rover%2C%20on%20the%20far%20side%20of%20the%20moon.%3Cp%3EChina%20National%20Space%20Administration%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMore%20than%2050%20years%20since%20Neil%20Armstrong%20landed%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20the%20world%20is%20racing%20to%20the%20lunar%20surface%20again.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENASA%20was%20slated%20to%20land%20astronauts%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%20earlier%20than%20China%20but%20has%20announced%20delays.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECongressional%20leaders%20on%20Wednesday%20fretted%20that%20China%20could%20land%20first%20and%20become%20a%20space%20power.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECongressional%20leaders%20on%20Wednesday%20warned%20of%20consequences%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20may%20face%20if%20they%20lose%20the%20new%20race%20to%20the%20moon%2C%20as%20the%20National%20American%20Space%20Agency%20announced%20delays%20to%20its%20crewed%20Artemis%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20worries%20were%20largely%20directed%20at%20efforts%20by%20China%20to%20forge%20its%20own%20space%20dominance%20and%20land%20astronauts%20on%20the%20moon%20in%20the%20next%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20is%20actively%20soliciting%20international%20partners%20for%20a%20lunar%20mission%2C%20a%20lunar%20research%20station%2C%20and%20has%20stated%20its%20ambition%20to%20have%20human%20astronauts%20on%20the%20surface%20by%202030%2C%26quot%3B%20Rep.%20Frank%20Lucas%20of%20Oklahoma%20said%20at%20a%20Science%2C%20Space%2C%20and%20Technology%20House%20Committee%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DP3ZFqd4DNlk%26ab_channel%3DHouseScience%252CSpace%252CandTechnologyCommittee%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehearing%20about%20the%20Artemis%20project.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20country%20that%20lands%20first%20will%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20set%20a%20precedent%20for%20whether%20future%20lunar%20activities%20are%20conducted%20with%20openness%20and%20transparency%2C%20or%20in%20a%20more%20restricted%20manner%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lucas%2C%20chairman%20of%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20other%20House%20representatives%20said%20they%20were%20concerned%20by%20the%20delays%20from%20NASA%2C%20which%20said%20on%20January%209%20that%20its%20Artemis%202%20launch%20%E2%80%94%20which%20aims%20to%20send%20US%20astronauts%20to%20the%20moon%20%E2%80%94%20would%20be%20postponed%20from%20November%202024%20to%20September%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENASA%20wants%20to%20fix%20issues%20before%20launch%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-artemis-megarocket-launches-orion-spaceship-toward-moon-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArtemis%20missions%3C%2Fa%3E%20comprise%20NASA's%20modern%20attempt%20to%20return%20to%20the%20moon%2C%20more%20than%2050%20years%20since%20Neil%20Armstrong%20first%20stepped%20foot%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20first%20launch%20was%20an%20uncrewed%20test%20flight%20in%202022%2C%20while%20its%20second%20launch%2C%20now%20scheduled%20for%202025%2C%20will%20send%20four%20astronauts%20around%20the%20moon%20but%20not%20on%20it.%20A%20third%20mission%2C%20now%20delayed%20from%202025%20to%20September%202026%2C%20would%20finally%20put%20American%20crews%20on%20the%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%20said%20it's%20had%20to%20delay%20the%20missions%20because%20it%20first%20needs%20to%20fix%20issues%20with%20its%20spacecraft's%20heat%20shield%2C%20which%20protects%20crews%20from%20extreme%20temperatures%20as%20they%20re-enter%20Earth's%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20space%20agency%20said%20it's%20also%20working%20on%20problems%20with%20the%20craft's%20life%20support%20system%20and%20emergency%20ejection%20system%2C%20which%20jettisons%20the%20crew%20capsule%20away%20from%20the%20rocket%20if%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Free%2C%20associate%20administrator%20at%20NASA%2C%20said%20at%20the%20delay%20announcement%20that%20safety%20is%20the%20agency's%20%26quot%3Bnumber%20one%20priority.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20will%20launch%20when%20we%20are%20ready%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Mike%20Griffin%2C%20a%20former%20chief%20of%20NASA%2C%20cast%20doubt%20on%20the%20agency's%20prediction%20that%20it%20could%20launch%20its%20man-on-the-moon%20mission%20in%20September%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Artemis%20circumlunar%20mission%20is%2C%20I%20think%2C%20very%20doable%20on%20the%20timescale%20that%20NASA%20has%20said%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Griffin%2C%20who%20was%20NASA%20administrator%20from%202005%20to%202009.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20Artemis%203%2C%20the%20landing%20mission%2C%20is%20at%20all%20realistically%20scheduled.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELawmakers%20foresee%20doom%20if%20China%20wins%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECongressional%20leaders%20on%20Wednesday%20acknowledged%20safety%20as%20a%20priority%20but%20repeatedly%20expressed%20nervousness%20over%20the%20delays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20no%20secret%20that%20China%20has%20a%20goal%20to%20surpass%20the%20United%20States%20by%202045%20as%20global%20leaders%20in%20space.%20We%20can't%20allow%20this%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20GOP%20Rep.%20Rich%20McCormick%20of%20Georgia%20said.%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20leading%20edge%20that%20we%20have%20in%20space%20technology%20will%20protect%20the%20United%20States.%20Not%20just%20the%20economy%2C%20but%20technologies%20that%20can%20benefit%20humankind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhoever%20controls%20space%20will%20control%20the%20destiny%20of%20this%20Earth%2C%26quot%3B%20Republican%20Rep.%20Bill%20Posey%20of%20Florida%20said%2C%20calling%20space%20the%20%26quot%3Bultimate%20military%20high%20ground.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20support%20Artemis%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Democratic%20Rep.%20Zoe%20Lofgren%20of%20California.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20want%20it%20to%20be%20successful%2C%20especially%20with%20China%20at%20our%20heels.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%2C%20however%2C%20has%20said%20that%20even%20with%20the%20delays%2C%20it%20should%20be%20comfortably%20ahead%20of%20China's%20national%20space%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20China%20has%20a%20very%20aggressive%20plan%2C%26quot%3B%20NASA%20Administrator%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.s