D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20frees%20Bengaluru%20girl%20from%20parents'%20illegal%20confinement%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705549203000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106944298%2Cimgsize-86498.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbengaluru%2Fsupreme-court-frees-bengaluru-girl-from-parents-illegal-confinement%2Farticleshow%2F106944209.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20criticizes%20the%20Karnataka%20high%20court%20for%20repeatedly%20adjourning%20the%20hearing%20on%20a%20habeas%20corpus%20petition%20filed%20by%20a%20Keralite%20man%20seeking%20the%20release%20of%20a%2025-year-old%20Tamil%20girl%20who%20was%20illegally%20confined%20by%20her%20parents.%20The%20girl%20and%20her%20parents%20appeared%20before%20the%20court%2C%20and%20the%20judges%20ruled%20that%20the%20girl's%20continued%20detention%20is%20illegal.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NiTi%20Aayog%20%E2%80%98Poverty%E2%80%99%20Stats%3A%20Serious%20Theoretical%2C%20Methodological%2C%20Empirical%20Questions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F18091934%2F49708038208_eff5e48c44_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog%20along%20with%20the%20UNDP%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.niti.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-01%2FMPI-22_NITI-Aayog20254.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereleased%20a%20discussion%20paper%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20findings%20of%20their%20Multidimensional%20Poverty%20Index%2C%20attempting%20to%20study%20the%20decline%20of%20poverty%20rates%20and%20the%20number%20of%20multidimensionally%20poor%20people%20in%20India%20across%20various%20time%20periods.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20serious%20theoretical%2C%20methodological%2C%20and%20empirical%20questions%20that%20remain%20yet%20to%20be%20settled%20on%20a%20subject%20that%20has%20severe%20policy%2C%20welfare%2C%20and%20state-ideological%20implications.%20Unfortunately%2C%20there%20is%20less%20of%20an%20intent%20or%20expressed%20willingness%20by%20the%20government%2C%20and%20those%20in%20NITI%20Aayog%20too%2C%20to%20engage%20with%20these%20issues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERather%2C%20what%20we%20see%20is%20a%20coercive%20push%20-unfortunately%20by%20different%20institutional%20ways%20and%20means-%20to%20keep%20beating%20down%20any%20possible%20data%20towards%20a%20rhetorical%20modelled%20reality%20painted%20by%20those%20who%20are%20obsessed%20with%20the%20view%20that%20%E2%80%98poverty%20reduction%20in%20India%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20consequential%20reality%2Fhappening%20in%20the%20last%20ten%20years%20(under%20the%20Modi%20government).%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELook%20closely%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20let%E2%80%99s%20look%20more%20closely%20at%20the%20Multidimensional%20Poverty%20Index%20created%20by%20NITI%20Aayog%20in%20alignment%20with%20the%20globally%20acclaimed%20Alkire%20Foster%20index%20methodology.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20National%20Multidimensional%20Poverty%20Index%20or%20NMPI%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fniti-aayong-national-poverty-indicator%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emeasures%20simultaneous%20deprivations%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20across%20three%20equally%20weighted%20dimensions%20of%20health%2C%20education%2C%20and%20standard%20of%20living%20that%20are%20represented%20by%2012%20sustainable%20development%20goals-aligned%20indicators%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fniti-aayong-national-poverty-indicator%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eaccording%20to%20NITI%20Aayog%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20include%20three%20Health%20(nutrition%2C%20child%20and%20adolescent%20mortality%2C%20maternal%20health)%3B%20two%20Education%20(years%20of%20schooling%2C%20school%20attendance)%3B%20and%20seven%20Standard%20of%20Living%20indicators%20(cooking%20fuel%2C%20sanitation%2C%20drinking%20water%2C%20electricity%2C%20housing%2C%20assets%2C%20and%20bank%20accounts).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20Index%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Emultidimensional%20poverty%20(MPI)%20in%20India%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fniti-aayong-national-poverty-indicator%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edeclined%20from%2029.17%25%20in%202013-14%20to%2011.28%25%20of%20the%20population%20in%202022-23%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20with%20about%2024.82%20crore%20people%20moving%20out%20of%20this%20bracket%20in%20nine%20years%20to%202022-23.%20They%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fniti-aayong-national-poverty-indicator%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ealso%20claim%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Bihar%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20registered%20the%20largest%20decline.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGiven%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FDeepanshu_1810%2Fstatus%2F1744180110079717532%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eparadoxical%20reflection%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emagical%20realism%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20shaping%20much%20of%20the%20underlying%20data%20around%20growth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20other%20developmental%20indicators%20and%20metrics%20on%20the%20Indian%20economy%2C%20and%20in%20particular%20terms%20to%20what%20we%20have%20seen%20in%20the%20quality%20(and%20politicisation)%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20statistical%20infrastructure%20over%20the%20last%2010%20years%2C%20one%20may%20ask%20the%20question%3A%20Are%20these%20claims-as%20projected%20by%20the%20MPI%20findings%2C%20credible%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEconomist%20Santosh%20Mehrotra%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20think%20so%20(and%20on%20grounds%20of%20empirical%20reasoning%20one%20can%20agree%20with%20his%20observations%20below).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20Mehrotra%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fniti-aayong-national-poverty-indicator%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0recent%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20column%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20no%20prima%20facie%20reason%20for%20assuming%20that%20the%207.9%25%20per%20annum%20GDP%20growth%20rate%20would%20deliver%20similar%20results%20(as%20applicable%20for%20MPI)%20to%20a%20period%20when%20the%20GDP%20growth%20rate%20for%20the%20recent%209%20years%20fell%20to%205.7%25%20per%20year.%20As%20though%20that%20presumption%20was%20not%20incredible%20enough%2C%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20paper%20goes%20further%2C%20drawing%20upon%20NFHS%205%20data%20for%202019%20and%202021%20(please%20note%2C%20not%202019%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A02021%20because%20the%20survey%20was%20stopped%20after%20data%20collection%20was%20stopped%20in%2022%20states%20due%20to%20COVID)%2C%20to%20project%20beyond%202021%20%E2%80%93%20to%202022%20and%202023.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20yet%20another%20linear%20projection%20was%20made%20by%20the%20authors%20to%20extend%20their%20conclusions%20to%20two%20years%20beyond%20the%20end%20of%20COVID.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20other%20words%2C%20it%20was%20using%20data%20for%20non-COVID%20years%20to%20extend%20non-COVID%20rates%20of%20improvement%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eafter%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0COVID%2C%20to%202022%20and%202023.%20Thus%20the%20question%20is%20legitimate%20as%20to%20whether%20that%20assumption%20is%20justified%20and%20credible%20or%20not.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20whole%20purpose%20of%20making%20the%20NMPI%20the%20poverty%20indicator%20for%20India%2C%20while%20consumption%20expenditure%20surveys%20were%20not%20done%20for%20eight%20years%20from%202014%20to%202022%2C%20is%20part%20of%20a%20political%20strategy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EEvidence%20for%20massive%20jump%20in%20poverty%20after%20COVID%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20part%20of%20our%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnesinfosphere.com%2Four-work%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EInfoSphere%20edition%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EGreat%20Poverty%20Debate%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20India%2C%20we%20discussed%20earlier%20how%20the%20disproportionate%20impact%20of%20the%20pandemic%20and%20the%20pandemic-induced%20lockdowns%20(and%20other%20restrictions)%20affected%20poorer%20households%20and%20states.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20analysis%20of%20household%20income%20data%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2FState_of_Working_India_2021-One_year_of_Covid-19.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eanalyzed%20by%20APU%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0revealed%20that%20the%20decline%20in%20incomes%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20period%20was%20higher%20for%20lower-income%20percentiles%20and%20gradually%20decreased%20for%20higher%20percentiles.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20bottom%2010%20percentiles%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-impact-of-covid-on-poverty-in-india-and-issues-regarding-its-estimates%23read-more%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexperienced%20a%20significant%2027%20percent%20drop%20in%20incomes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20while%20the%20decline%20was%2023%25%20for%20the%2040th%20to%2050th%20percentiles%20and%2022%25%20for%20the%20top%2010%20percentiles.%20Furthermore%2C%20there%20was%20a%2015-percentage%20point%20increase%20in%20rural%20areas%20and%20nearly%2020%20percentage%20points%20in%20urban%20areas.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-impact-of-covid-on-poverty-in-india-and-issues-regarding-its-estimates%23read-more%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eincome%20declines%20in%20urban%20areas%20were%20relatively%20higher%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20compared%20to%20rural%20areas%2C%20the%20difference%20between%20poor%20and%20relatively%20well-off%20households%20may%20seem%20small%20in%20percentage%20points.%20However%2C%20it%20represents%20a%20significant%20decline%20in%20absolute%20terms%2C%20exacerbating%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20vulnerable%20populations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fopinion%2Fonline-views%2Fa-comprehensive-assessment-of-deprivation-must-consider-non-monetary-metrics-too-11704632189911.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enon-monetary%20deprivations%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(as%20measured%20by%20a%20vulnerable%20group%E2%80%99s%20access%20to%20education%2C%20healthcare%2C%20nutrition%20etc.)%2C%20one%20can%20see%20a%20sharp%20rise%20in%20absolute%20and%20relative%20poverty%20measures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fissues%2Ffood%2Fcovid19%2F2022-07-07%2Fsubmission-rtf-covid-ga-76-cso-asiachapter-3-en.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EHunger%20Watch%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0national%20survey%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Food%20campaign%2C%20a%20crisis%20emerged%20in%20December%202021%20%E2%80%93%20January%202022%20due%20to%20declining%20incomes%20and%20severe%20food%20insecurity%2C%20especially%20among%20the%20economically%20vulnerable%20and%20marginalized%20sections%20of%20society%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3E%2080%25%20of%20people%20reported%20some%20form%20of%20food%20insecurity%2C%20and%2025%25%20reported%20severe%20food%20insecurity%2C%20such%20as%20skipping%20meals%2C%20cutting%20back%20on%20food%2C%20running%20out%20of%20food%2C%20not%20eating%20throughout%20the%20day%20and%20going%20to%20bed%20hungry%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3E%2041%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20the%20nutritional%20value%20of%20their%20diet%20had%20worsened%20compared%20to%C2%A0%20pre-pandemic%20times%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3E67%25%20of%20people%20could%20not%20afford%20cooking%20gas%20in%20the%20month%20before%20the%20survey%2C%20further%20reducing%20their%20ability%20to%20cook%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlso%2C%20a%20report%20by%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2021%2F03%2F18%2Fin-the-pandemic-indias-middle-class-shrinks-and-poverty-spreads-while-china-sees-smaller-changes%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EPew%20Research%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3ECentre%20highlights%20that%20around%2075%20million%20more%20people%20in%20India%20fell%20into%20poverty%20in%20year%202022%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic-induced%20economic%20recession%2C%20compared%20with%20what%20it%20would%20have%20been%20without%20the%20outbreak.%20That%20number%20for%20India%20accounts%20for%20nearly%2060%25%20of%20the%20global%20increase%20in%20poverty%20in%202020.%20In%20that%20study%2C%20it%20defined%20the%20poor%20as%20people%20who%20live%20on%20%242%20or%20less%20daily.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbsolute%20Increase%20in%20Poverty%20in%20India%20due%20to%20the%C2%A0%20Pandemic%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E75%20million%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cstrong%3EGlobal%20Increase%20in%20Poverty%20(2020)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E125%20million%20(which%20implies%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%2075%20million%20increase%20contributed%2060%25%20to%20global%20poverty%20increase)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESource%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnesinfosphere.com%2Four-work%5C%22%3EInfosphere%20CNES%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Data%20from%20Pew%20Research%20Centre)%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMore%20recently%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2FState_of_Working_India_2021-One_year_of_Covid-19.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20State%20of%20Working%20India%20Study%20conducted%20by%20Azim%20Premji%20University%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eoffers%20valuable%20insights%20into%20the%20impact%20of%20COVID-19%20on%20Indian%20households.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20study%20reveals%20that%20from%20March%20to%20October%202020%2C%20households%20experienced%20a%20significant%20loss%20of%20income%2C%20with%20an%20average%20decline%20of%2022%25%20in%20cumulative%20income.%20However%2C%20the%20income%20loss%20was%20more%20pronounced%20among%20poorer%20households%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20substantial%20increase%20in%20poverty%20rates%20across%20the%20country.%20The%20APU%20analysis%20primarily%20relies%20on%20monthly%20household%20income%20data%20from%20the%20CMIE-CPHS%2C%20along%20with%20data%20from%20the%20India%20Working%20Survey%20(IWS)%20and%20Azim%20Premji%20University%20Covid%20Livelihoods%20Phone%20Survey%20(CLIPS).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconsumerpyramidsdx.cmie.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECMIE-CPHS%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Emethod%20refers%20to%20the%20Consumer%20Pyramids%20Households%20Survey%20(CPHS)%20which%20is%20a%20comprehensive%20and%20nationally%20representative%20survey%20conducted%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20the%20Indian%20Economy%20since%202014.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERegardless%20of%20which%20method%20one%20uses%2C%20the%20larger%20issue%20underlying%20the%20methodological%20concern%20to%20poverty%20measurement%20in%20India%20is%20a%20crisis%20of%20poverty%20(and%20welfare)%20statistics%20in%20a%20rapidly%20politicising%20and%20compromised%20statistical%20infrastructure%2C%20making%20any%20critical%20scrutiny%20erroneously%20difficult.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20crisis%20of%20poverty-statistics%20in%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20India%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPoverty%20estimates%2C%20as%20rightly%20argued%20by%20Himanshu%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAre%20not%20just%20an%20academic%20exercise%20but%20are%20crucial%20parameters%20to%20judge%20policy%20outcomes%20and%20the%20overall%20functioning%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20own%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20research%20team%2C%20while%20creating%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjgu.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com%2Fjslh%2FReport%2BAEI%2BFinal.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAccess%20Equality%20Index%20(AEI)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20exploring%20nonmonetary%20forms%20of%20deprivations%20had%20discussed%20the%20wider%20implications%20of%20states%20across%20India%20being%20asymmetrically%20ranked%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjgu.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com%2Fjslh%2FReport%2BAEI%2BFinal.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eon%20providing%20%E2%80%98access%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20basic%20social%2C%20economic%20services%20(from%20food%2C%20healthcare%2C%20education%2C%20job%20security%2C%20finance%2C%20legal%20recourse-to%20name%20a%20few).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20unfortunately%20happening%20is%20that%20research%20in%20Indian%20social%20sciences%2C%20not%20just%20in%20economics%2C%20has%20broadly%20transitioned%20to%20%E2%80%98proving%20hypothesis%20I%20or%20II%E2%80%99%20rather%20than%20seeing%20the%20%E2%80%98data%20for%20what%20it%20actually%20is%E2%80%99%20and%20then%20making%20reasonable%20conclusions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20data%20is%20used%20for%20theory-validation%20rather%20than%20the%20other%20way%20around.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThere%20is%20more%20to%20it%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGrowth%20alone%20is%20a%20bad%20indicator%20of%20quality%20of%20life%20as%20it%20fails%20to%20tell%20us%20how%20deprived%20people%20are%20doing.%20Thinking%20of%20developmental%20goal%20in%20terms%20of%20utility%20has%20perhaps%20the%20only%20merit%20of%20looking%20at%20what%20processes%20do%20for%20people%20in%20letting%20them%20%E2%80%98be%E2%80%99%20what%20%E2%80%98they%20want%20to%20be%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPoverty%2C%20for%20worse%2C%20represents%20a%20state%20of%20powerlessness%20%E2%80%93%20lack%20of%20opportunity%20and%20possible%20upward-mobility%20for%20an%20identified%20group%2C%20one%20that%20often%20lives%2Fpositions%20itself%20on%20the%20bottom%20of%20consumption-income%20pyramid.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPart%20of%20the%20reason%20there%20are%20conflicting%20estimates%20of%20poverty%20for%20the%20same%20period%20is%20the%20loss%20of%20reliable%20data%20and%20a%20yardstick%20to%20measure%20poverty%20and%20inequality%20after%202011-12.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20a%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Epoverty%20of%20statistics%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0that%20crowds%20out%20any%20meaningful%20policy%20or%20academic%20discourse%20on%20the%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Estatistics%20of%20poverty%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%93%20and%20much%20of%20other%20social%20policy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEconomists%2C%20dare%20I%20say%2C%20are%20increasingly%20toeing%20the%20government%20narrative%20when%20it%20suits%20them%2C%20and%20oft%20dismiss%20any%20critical%20insight%20that%20brings%20the%20government%20(or%20its%20own%20policy-methodology)%20to%20account.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fsocial-policy-debates-aimed-at-making-the-govt-look-good-are-missing-clarity-and-reason%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egovernment%20economists%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20-along%20with%20those%20writing%20to%20align%20with%20the%20regime%E2%80%99s%20rhetoric%20and%20ideology%20who%20constantly%20argue%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Fbyline%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98proxy%E2%80%99%20indicators%20on%20poverty%20reflect%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%98a%20fall%E2%80%99%20in%20its%20actual%20estimate%2C%20while%20others%20weighing%20their%20evidence%20against%20the%20%E2%80%98facts%E2%80%99%20show%20contrary%20results%20(see%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-great-india-poverty-debate-double-crisis-of-data-theory-plagues-analysts%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehere%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-impact-of-covid-on-poverty-in-india-and-issues-regarding-its-estimates%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehere%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20a%20more%20detailed%20discussion%20of%20the%20author%20on%20this).%20It%E2%80%99s%20because%20of%20this%20reason%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fsocial-policy-debates-aimed-at-making-the-govt-look-good-are-missing-clarity-and-reason%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esocial%20policy%20debates%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20India-not%20just%20on%20poverty%20but%20so%20many%20other%20vital%20welfare%20issues-lack%20both%2C%20clarity%20and%20critical%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMore%20importantly%2C%20having%20closely%20worked%20on%20development%20indices%2C%20while%20creating%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjgu.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com%2Fjslh%2FReport%2BAEI%2BFinal.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAccess(In)Equality%20Index%20in%202021%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20updating%20its%20input-output%20indicators%20more%20recently%2C%20one%20becomes%20aware%20of%20choice-issues%20related%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98form%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98structure%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98design%E2%80%99%20limitations%20of%20such%20hand-picked%2C%20crafted%20metrics%20and%20what%20they%20may%20directionally%20-if%20not%20empirically%2C%20imply.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20country%20where%20we%20haven%E2%80%99t%20seen%20the%20regular%20conduct%20and%20release%20of%20national%20consumption%20expenditure%20survey%20data%20(from%20which%20poverty%20measurement%20principally%20happened%20in%20the%20past)%20or%20the%20census%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Fbyline%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethere%20is%20room%20for%20much%20debate%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20whether%20the%20Modi%20government%20is%20honest%20about%20its%20intent%20to%20show%2Freflect%20the%20%E2%80%98truth%E2%80%99%20of%20poverty%20performance%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPoverty%20and%20income%20distribution%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fsocial-policy-debates-aimed-at-making-the-govt-look-good-are-missing-clarity-and-reason%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eare%20issues%20for%20public%20discussion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20much%20as%20they%20are%20instruments%20of%20governance%20and%20public%20policy%20for%20an%20economy%20which%20still%20has%20a%20substantial%20population%20that%E2%80%99s%20financially%20vulnerable%20even%20if%20not%20officially%20poor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnless%20we%20take%20conscious%20measures%2C%20at%20the%20level%20of%20state-authority%2C%20to%20consciously%20depoliticise%20data%20and%20encourage%20independent%20critical%20scrutiny%20of%20existing%20(and%20new)%20methodologies%20of%20public%20data%20accounting%2Fanalysis%2C%20there%20is%20little%20hope%20on%20what%20we%20might%20do%20on%20both%20social%20and%20economic%20policy.%20The%20policy%20making%20framework%20and%20those%20behind%20social%20policy%20evaluation%20can%20do%20better%20in%20making%20the%20%E2%80%98discourse%E2%80%99%20more%20analytically%20coherent%20than%20operate%20under%20constant%20cycles%20of%20confusion.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20economics%20and%20director%2C%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20OP%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20essay%E2%80%99s%20empirical%20data%20and%20findings%20are%20drawn%20from%20the%20previous%202023%20investigative%20research%20undertaken%20by%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnesinfosphere.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EInfoSphere%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20team%20on%20poverty%20assessment%20in%20India%20using%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnesinfosphere.com%2F_files%2Fugd%2F85c814_af67678d17f640a5bc58ca162526552d.pdf%3Findex%3Dtrue%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20pre-covid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnesinfosphere.com%2F_files%2Fugd%2F85c814_4f20d0ceed2b46a7982b027370c74d65.pdf%3Findex%3Dtrue%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epost-covid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20difference%20in%20difference%20perspective.%20For%20details%2C%20please%20review%20InfoSphere%E2%80%99s%20work%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnesinfosphere.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehere%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20more%20details.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ETeam%20credits%20feature%20Amisha%20Singh%2C%20Aditi%20Desai%20as%20Senior%20Research%20Analysts%20with%20CNES%20and%20team%20leads%20of%20InfoSphere%20team.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705548637000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F18085659%2F3294763957_ff57439581_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fniti-aayog-poverty-covid%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20debilitating%20impact%20of%20COVID%20on%20poverty%20is%20mischievously%20missing%20in%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20controversial%20MPI%20findings.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fniti-aayog-poverty-covid%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2224%20Chinese%20warplanes%20around%20Taiwan%20in%20first%20show%20of%20force%20since%20poll%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705548592000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106944111%2Cimgsize-696674.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fchinese-warplanes-around-taiwan-first-show-of-force-since-poll%2Farticleshow%2F106943955.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F106943955.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EMore%20than%2020%20Chinese%20warplanes%20were%20detected%20around%20Taiwan%2C%20with%2011%20crossing%20a%20sensitive%20median%20line%20separating%20the%20self-ruled%20island%20from%20China%2C%20Taipei's%20defence%20ministry%20