%20eons-long%20collision%20that%20created%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Findia-china-buying-new-light-tanks-for-himalayan-mountain-warfare-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Himalayas%2C%20the%20world's%20tallest%20mountain%20range%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20may%20also%20be%20splitting%20Tibet%20apart%20into%20two%20pieces%2C%20new%20research%20suggests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20collision%20of%20the%20Indian%20and%20Eurasian%20tectonic%20plates%20began%2060%20million%20years%20ago%20when%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-shocked-to-discover-alaska-isnt-an-island-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eisland%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20now%20known%20as%20India%2C%20crashed%20into%20the%20continent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20edge%20of%20the%20Eurasian%20plate%20crumpled%20upward%20as%20India%20pressed%20into%20it%2C%20thrusting%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhundreds-of-bodies-himalayan-skeleton-lake-photos-2019-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHimalayas%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20existence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228229%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20landmark%20Potala%20Palace%20is%20seen%20after%20a%20snowfall%20on%20April%2025%2C%202023%20in%20Lhasa%2C%20Tibet%20Autonomous%20Region%20of%20China.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a84f7a6979d737182428ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225486%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20landmark%20Potala%20Palace%20is%20seen%20after%20a%20snowfall%20in%20Lhasa%2C%20Tibet%20Autonomous%20Region%20of%20China.%3Cp%3EGongga%20Laisong%2FChina%20News%20Service%2FVCG%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20slow-motion%20collision%20is%20still%20ongoing%2C%20meaning%20the%20Eurasian%20plate%20is%20still%20crumpling%20and%20the%20Himalayas%20continue%20to%20grow.%20But%20scientists%20haven't%20been%20sure%20where%20exactly%20the%20Indian%20plate%20was%20going.%20Is%20it%20sliding%20directly%20under%20the%20Eurasian%20plate%2C%20skimming%20its%20underside%3F%20Or%20is%20it%20plunging%20deeper%20into%20the%20layer%20of%20mantle%20below%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20research%20paints%20a%20chaotic%20picture%20where%20both%20things%20are%20happening%3A%20The%20Indian%20plate%20is%20peeling%20apart%2C%20with%20its%20buoyant%20upper%20crust%20detaching%20from%20its%20dense%20bottom%20layer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20that%20process%20is%20creating%20a%20vertical%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatlantic-ocean-widening-geologic-forces-earth-crust-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esplit%20in%20the%20plate%3C%2Fa%3E%20beneath%20Tibet%2C%20as%20the%20peeling%20section%20tears%20away%20from%20an%20adjacent%20region%20that's%20not%20peeling%2C%20the%20new%20findings%20suggest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222289%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22man%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20blue%20wooden%20one-story%20house%20leaning%20off%20the%20side%20of%20a%20cliff%20with%20green%20hills%20in%20the%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a8739fdcdb354a985876b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20man%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20his%20house%2C%20which%20was%20damaged%20by%206.9%20magnitude%20earthquake%2C%20at%20the%20Himalayan%20Mangan%20village%20in%20India.%3Cp%3EStringer%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20a%20giant%20crack%20is%20going%20to%20open%20across%20the%20surface%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdalai-lama-suck-my-tongue-boy-innocent-tibetan-leader-says-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETibet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Rather%2C%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20more%20going%20on%20deep%20beneath%20the%20surface%20than%20scientists%20realized.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20this%20%26quot%3Bslab%20tear%26quot%3B%20under%20Tibet%20could%20drive%20hazardous%20earthquakes%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20has%20not%20yet%20undergone%20peer%20review%2C%20but%20it%20was%20presented%20at%20the%20meeting%20of%20the%20American%20Geophysical%20Union%20in%20December%2C%20and%20a%20pre-print%20version%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fessopenarchive.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.22541%2Fessoar.170000377.75686509%2Fv1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20published%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20didn't%20know%20continents%20could%20behave%20this%20way%20and%20that%20is%2C%20for%20solid%20earth%20science%2C%20pretty%20fundamental%2C%26quot%3B%20Douwe%20van%20Hinsbergen%2C%20an%20Utrecht%20University%20geodynamicist%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20research%2C%20told%20the%20magazine%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2Ftectonic-plate-under-tibet-may-be-splitting-two%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScience%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimon%20Klemperer%2C%20a%20geophysicist%20at%20Stanford%20University%2C%20worked%20with%20colleagues%20at%20three%20Chinese%20research%20institutions%20to%20piece%20together%20this%20picture%20of%20the%20plates.%20They%20studied%20earthquake%20waves%20that%20passed%20through%20the%20deep%20layers%20below%2C%20examined%20the%20locations%20of%20earthquakes%20under%20Tibet%2C%20and%20analyzed%20gases%20rising%20into%20hot%20springs%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20speculate%20that%20this%20slab%20tear%20may%20divide%20the%20mountain%20chain%20along%20its%20length%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20scientists%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagu.confex.com%2Fagu%2Ffm23%2Fmeetingapp.cgi%2FPaper%2F1238166%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esummary%20of%20their%20findings%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Himalayas%20run%20along%20the%20southern%20edge%20of%20Tibet%2C%20which%20sits%20on%20a%20plateau%20about%2013%2C000%20ft%20above%20sea%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20no%20direct%20link%20has%20been%20documented%2C%20these%20deep%20shifts%20in%20the%20earth%20might%20affect%20earthquakes%20near%20the%20surface%2C%20van%20Hinsbergen%20told%20Science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20long%20thought%20this%20type%20of%20tearing%20could%20happen%20when%20continental%20plates%20collide%2C%20but%20this%20is%20the%20first%20time%20it's%20been%20%26quot%3Bcaught%20in%20the%20act%2C%26quot%3B%20van%20Hinsbergen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftibet-maybe-splitting-apart-himalayan-mountains-grow-tectonic-plates-study-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705546608000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a8507d6979d73718242948%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftibet-maybe-splitting-apart-himalayan-mountains-grow-tectonic-plates-study-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Himalayas%20continue%20to%20grow%20as%20the%20Indian%20and%20Eurasian%20plates%20collide%2C%20but%20scientists%20say%20the%20process%20may%20be%20peeling%20apart%20the%20plate%20beneath%20Tibet.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis%2CMorgan%20McFall-Johnsen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftibet-maybe-splitting-apart-himalayan-mountains-grow-tectonic-plates-study-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hyd%E2%80%99s%20jumbo%20laddu%20on%20sweet%20%E2%80%98pilgrimage%E2%80%99%20to%20Ram%20Mandir%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705546454000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106949384%2Cimgsize-1924349.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2Fhyds-jumbo-laddu-on-sweet-pilgrimage-to-ram-mandir%2Farticleshow%2F106942379.cms%2