Bryce%20doesn't%20reach%20Hel%2C%20instead%20finding%20herself%20in%20a%20strange%2C%20idyllic%20land.%20That%20land%20is%20Prythian%2C%20where%20the%20%26quot%3BA%20Court%20of%20Thorns%20and%20Roses%26quot%3B%20series%20is%20set.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBryce%20is%20only%20formally%20introduced%20to%20Rhysand%20in%20%26quot%3BHouse%20of%20Sky%20and%20Breath%2C%26quot%3B%20though%20she%20appears%20to%20interact%20with%20Feyre%20Archeron%2C%20Nesta%20Archeron%2C%20Amren%2C%20Cassian%2C%20and%20Azriel.%20Feyre%20and%20Rhysand%20are%20the%20High%20Lord%20and%20High%20Lady%20of%20the%20Night%20Court%2C%20and%20the%20others%20serve%20in%20their%20court.%20Nesta%20is%20also%20one%20of%20Feyre's%20sisters%2C%20and%20she%20is%20mated%20to%20Cassian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20court%20members%20are%20fae%2C%20though%20Amren%20used%20to%20be%20another%20more%20powerful%20creature%20before%20she%20sacrificed%20that%20part%20of%20herself%20during%20a%20war%20in%20%26quot%3BA%20Court%20of%20Wings%20and%20Ruin.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBryce's%20interactions%20with%20the%20Night%20Court%20are%20brief%20in%20%26quot%3BHOSAB%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsarah-j-maas-halloween-costumes-acotar-throne-of-glass-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMaas%3C%2Fa%3E%20revealed%20several%20connections%20between%20%26quot%3BCrescent%20City%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20%26quot%3BACOTAR%26quot%3B%20universe%20in%20the%20chapter.%20First%2C%20Bryce%20thinks%20Rhysand%20is%20her%20brother%20when%20she%20first%20sees%20him%20because%20he%20looks%20nearly%20identical%20to%20Ruhn.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20Starsword%20lights%20up%20when%20placed%20next%20to%20Azriel's%20knife%2C%20Truth-Teller%2C%20indicating%20it%20is%20Truth-Teller's%20long-lost%20twin%20weapon%2C%20Gwydion%2C%20which%20is%20mentioned%20several%20times%20in%20%26quot%3BACOTAR.%26quot%3B%20Likewise%2C%20Bryce%20discovers%20she%20can%20communicate%20with%20Rhysand%20and%20Amren%20b